cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on sensor networks and proposes a new gossiping scheme for aggregation that is more efficient than previous protocols. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for aggregation in sensor networks that utilizes geographic information. This falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the energy consumption of gossip algorithms in sensor networks and proposes a more efficient scheme. This falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for aggregation in sensor networks. This falls under the scope of distributed computing. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the accuracy of the proposed gossiping scheme and its ability to compute the true average to a certain level of accuracy. This falls under the scope of information theory.
